A university student was on Wednesday night killed in her hostel.  Getrude Chepkoech, a first-year student at Laikipia University, is said to have been stabbed to death by a boyfriend to one of her friends.  Her attacker is said to have stabbed Chepkoech several times before turning the knife on himself. He died at Nyahururu County Hospital where he had been admitted.  Nyahururu sub-county police commander Mary Kiema said Chepkoech was alone in the house when the man attacked.   Laikipia University student killed by roommate’s boyfriend  Laikipia University students rue missed chances due to delayed graduation  Former teacher gets degree at 74  Kipchoge to receive honorary degree from Laikipa University  Educaton Cabinet secretary Dr. Matiangi lifts ban on Kisii University   Samburu moran wakabili polisi  Educaton Cabinet secretary Dr. Matiangi lifts ban on Kisii University  By Daniel Chege | 5 hours ago By Lynn Kolongei | 5 hours ago By Collins Kweyu | 5 hours ago By Jael Mboga | 10 hours ago